<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1319,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
The current study confirmed two 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Macleay" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[552,745,1319,1345]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[552,745,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Pastinachus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[765,867,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[435,1148,1132,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@9.[428,1160,1123,1813]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dorsal image of Pastinachus cf. ater from Coxâ€™s Bazar (Male, DW= 33.02 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448242" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448242/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Figure 7</figureCitation>
) specimens in 
<collectingCountry box="[1049,1180,1319,1345]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1244,1401,1319,1345]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="generic">18 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Last, Manjaji &amp; Yearsley" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,434,1355,1381]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="solocirostris">
<emphasis box="[151,434,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Pastinachus solocirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[449,546,1355,1381]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,890,914]" captionTargetBox="[465,1124,193,856]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[453,1134,181,866]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Dorsal image of Pastinachus solocirostris caught from southcentral Bangladesh (Male, DW= 71.12 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448244/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). It is assumed that, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Macleay" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[777,850,1355,1380]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[777,850,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been previously reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1248,1379,1355,1381]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Roy et al. 2015)" baseAuthorityName="Roy" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sephen">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P. sephen</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roy, B. J. &amp; Singha, N. K. &amp; Rhaman, M. G. &amp; Ali, A. H. M. H." box="[243,421,1390,1417]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" pagination="343 - 367" refId="ref7818" refString="Roy, B. J., Singha, N. K., Rhaman, M. G. &amp; Ali, A. H. M. H. (2015) Status and recorded of sharks and rays in the Bay of Bengal of Bangladesh Region. Brazilian Journal of Biological Sciences, 2 (4), 343 - 367." type="journal article" year="2015">
Roy 
<emphasis box="[298,354,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, though a recent taxonomic study found that 
<taxonomicName box="[932,1037,1391,1417]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sephen">
<emphasis box="[932,1037,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P. sephen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only found in the Western Indian Ocean (Red Sea to 
<collectingCountry box="[372,469,1427,1454]" name="Pakistan" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Last, P. R. &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M." box="[492,873,1427,1453]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" pagination="115 - 127" refId="ref7350" refString="Last, P. R. &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. (2010) Description of a new stingray, Pastinachus gracilicaudus sp. nov. (Elasmobranchii: Myliobatiformes), based on material from the Indo - Malay Archipelago. In: Last, P. R., White, W. T. &amp; Pogonoski, J. J. (Eds.), Descriptions of New Sharks and Rays from Borneo. CSIRO Marine and Atmospheric Research Paper 032. CSIRO Marine and Atmospheric Research, Hobart, pp. 115 - 127." type="book chapter" year="2010">Last &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto 2010</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<specimenCount box="[1009,1181,1427,1453]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
were morphologically very close to 
<taxonomicName box="[299,404,1463,1489]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sephen">
<emphasis box="[299,404,1463,1489]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P. sephen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and referred to as 
<taxonomicName box="[608,748,1463,1489]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sephen">
<emphasis box="[608,630,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[670,748,1463,1489]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">sephen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[762,858,1463,1489]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1778,1802]" captionTargetBox="[466,1128,950,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-42@10.[447,1141,938,1754]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Dorsal image of Pastinachus cf. sephen (Female juvenile. DW= 20.32cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448246" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448246/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Figure 9</figureCitation>
) needing further taxonomic work. We also recorded 
<specimenCount box="[151,322,1499,1525]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of a third species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruppell in Ruppell" authorityYear="1828" box="[582,719,1499,1525]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[582,719,1499,1525]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Pastinachus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are morphologically consistent with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Last &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto" authorityYear="2010" box="[1243,1429,1499,1525]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilicaudus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1429,1499,1525]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">P. gracilicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further taxonomic examination is required, however, as differences were found between the NADH2 sequences of the 
<collectingCountry box="[230,361,1571,1597]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
as compared to Borneo specimens. This species is tentatively referred to as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Last &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto" authorityYear="2010" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinachus" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilicaudus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1397,1571,1597]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Pastinachus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[151,305,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">gracilicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[320,433,1607,1633]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,899,923]" captionTargetBox="[470,1114,192,865]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[460,1128,181,875]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal image of Pastinachus cf. gracilicaudus caught from southcentral Bangladesh (Pregnant female, DW= 83.82 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448248" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448248/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Figure 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
